svg.text: This product is a seven-compartment ​medicine tray. It is seven because it has ​one slot for each day of the week. At the ​beginning of the week the patient can fill ​up each slot with

the medicine for that ​day and then have it all ready to take ​when that day comes. It is also great as a ​tool to remember whether the medicine ​was taken or not. This particular pill ​reminder has two special features. It has labels on each slot for the day of the week. That ​way it is easy to organize and break out dosages by day. Also, it has a locking feature so ​that the patient can prevent anyone who shouldn’t be getting into the pills from getting to ​them. At the same time a caretaker could lock the pill reminder to prevent a patient from ​getting to the pills if there were issues with that. Lastly, because of the low cost of the pill ​reminder a patient could get one for each day’s dose. For example, one tray for morning ​medicine, and one for night medicine. Reflection: Your thoughts, comments and lingering questions about this product/service:​I think this is probably the simplest form of a medication reminder and one of the easiest. ​However, what can be difficult is filling up the slots a week ahead of time. This would take ​diligence on the patient’s part in order to actually set it up properly every week. The system ​also relies entirely on the patient or whoever is setting it up.
